name: Christmas Factor – Factor IX diamond
description:
The Christmas factor, or factor IX, is a protein whose first case of deficiency was discovered in the 1950s in a young patient named Stephen Christmas. Factor IX is a critical enzyme for the formation of stable blood clots. Deficiency of factor IX results in hemophilia B.
